<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T03:00:00-05:00" n="820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control
                                    (Rumania)/7–2645: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 820<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Acting Representative in
                                        Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Melbourne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d820fn1">The gist
                                        of this message was included in telegram No. 140 of July 27
                                        from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No.
                                        800.00 Summaries/7–2745).</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26T10:00:00+02:00">July 26, 1945—10 a.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>504. Soviet officials of the Allied Control Commission on July 24
                                    verbally stated that the program providing for a revised
                                    operation of Allied Control Commission as reported in <persName corresp="#p_SBGCTVR1">General Schuyler</persName>’s <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> telegram July 16 No <gloss target="#t_M1">M</gloss>–1250<note n="2" xml:id="d820fn2">See <ref target="#d797fn3">document No. 797, footnote
                                            3</ref>.</note> did not apply to this mission (This is
                                    504) with respect to permitting it to determine unilaterally the
                                    number of its personnel.</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MRM1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Melbourne</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>